Atlanta Falcons wordmark.svg\n| year            = 2020\n| record          =\n| division_place  =\n| coach           = [[Dan Quinn (American football)|Dan Quinn]]\n| owner           = [[Arthur Blank]]\n| general manager = [[Thomas Dimitroff]]\n| stadium         = [[Mercedes-Benz Stadium]]\n| playoffs        =\n| pro bowlers     =\n| uniform         = Atlanta falcons unif20.png\n| shortnavlink    = Falcons seasons\n}}\nThe [[2020 NFL season|2020 season]] will be the [[Atlanta Falcons]]' upcoming 55th season in the [[National Football League]], their fourth playing their home games at [[Mercedes-Benz Stadium]] and their sixth under [[List of Atlanta Falcons head coaches|head coach]] [[Dan Quinn (American football)|Dan Quinn]].\n\nFor the first time since the [[2003 Atlanta Falcons season|2003 season]], the Falcons will be sporting new uniforms, which were unveiled on April 8, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.atlantafalcons.com/new-uniforms-2020?campaign=sf:fanshare:facebook|title=Official Website of the Atlanta Falcons Football Club|website=www.atlantafalcons.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-09}}</ref>\n\nThe Falcons will attempt to improve on their [[2019 Atlanta Falcons season|7-9 season]] from the previous year and make the playoffs for the first time since [[2017 NFL season|2017]].\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Draft==\n{{main|2020 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|year=2020|border=2}}\"| 2020 Atlanta Falcons Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College !! Notes\n|-\n! [[List of Atlanta Falcons first-round draft picks|1]] ||16\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n! 2 || 47\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n! 3 || 78\n| <!--PLAYER-->|| <!--POSITION-->|| <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | 4 || 119\n| <!--PLAYER-->|| <!--POSITION-->|| <!--COLLEGE--> || <!--NOTES-->\n|-\n!143\n|<!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 Baltimore Ravens season|Baltimore]]\n|-\n! 7 || 228\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE--> || from [[2020 Philadelphia Eagles season|Philadelphia]]\n|}\n\n'''Trades'''\n* The Falcons traded wide receiver [[Mohamed Sanu]] to the [[2019 New England Patriots season|New England Patriots]] in exchange for a second-round selection.\n* The Falcons traded the second-round selection from New England and a fifth-round selection to the [[2020 Baltimore Ravens season|Baltimore Ravens]] in exchange for tight end [[Hayden Hurst]] and a fourth-round selection.\n* The Falcons traded a sixth-round selection and linebacker [[Duke Riley (American football)|Duke Riley]] to the [[2019 Philadelphia Eagles season|Philadelphia Eagles]] in exchange for safety [[Johnathan Cyprien]] and a seventh-round selection.\n\n==Staff==\n{{Atlanta Falcons staff}}\n\n==Current roster==\n{{Atlanta Falcons roster}}\n\n==Preseason==\nThe Falcons' preseason opponents and schedule will be announced in the spring.\n\n==Regular season==\n<!--===Schedule===-->\n===2020 opponents===\nListed below are the Falcons' opponents for [[2020 NFL season|2020]]. Exact dates and times will be announced in the spring.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Opponents Determined |url=https://nflcommunications.com/Pages/2020-Opponents-Determined.aspx |work=NFL Communications |date=December 30, 2019 |accessdate=December 30, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}}\"| Category !! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}}\" width=200px| Home !! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}}\" width=200px| Away\n|-\n| '''Division opponents'''<br>([[NFC South]]) || colspan=2| [[2020 Carolina Panthers season|Carolina Panthers]]<br>[[2020 New Orleans Saints season|New Orleans Saints]]<br>[[2020 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]\n|-\n| '''Conference 